In this section, we present the result of the distribution of gender identification methods in the papers in our corpus. Compared to the author name disambiguation methods, which usually involve a single method for disambiguating authors' names, numerous studies relied on multiple methods for identifying authors' gender identities. We found that 45/70 (64.3%) [68; 8; 46; 48; 74;
